@startuml layers
title API Layered Architecture Diagram

rectangle "User Interface Layer" {
    actor "User" as User
    rectangle "Frontend (Web/App)" as Frontend
}

rectangle "API Layer" {
    rectangle "API Gateway" as APIGateway
}

rectangle "Business Logic Layer" {
    rectangle "Rate Limiter" as RateLimiter
    rectangle "Core System" as System
    rectangle "SMS Service" as SMSService
    rectangle "Logging Service" as LoggingService
}

rectangle "Data Layer" {
    database "Database" as Database
}

User -> Frontend: Submit phone number\nRequest code\nVerify code
Frontend -> APIGateway: REST API Calls\n(e.g., /phone/submit)
APIGateway -d-> RateLimiter: Check rate limits
RateLimiter --> APIGateway: Allow/Deny

APIGateway -> System: Process request
System -d-> Database: Store/Fetch user data
System -u-> SMSService: Send confirmation code
System -> LoggingService: Log events
SMSService -> LoggingService: Log SMS status

Frontend <-- APIGateway: Responses\n(200 OK, 400 Error, etc.)

@enduml
